==English==
===Etymology===
From a story by an anonymous author published in 1760 called ''The Life and Adventures of a Cat'' in which the male cat, then known as a [[ram]] cat, was called Tom.  (Reference: Desmond Morris, ''Catwatching''.)
===Noun===
'''tomcat'''

#A [[tom]], a male [[cat]].

====Translations====
:''See under'' [[tom]].
